CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Business Regulation – Charitable Organizations – Audit and Review Thresholds
3 FOR the purpose of increasing the minimum gross income amounts from charitable
4 contributions at which a charitable organization must include a certain audit or a
5 certain review with the charitable organization’s registration statement; increasing
6 the amount of cash receipts from charitable contributions the Secretary of State may
7 accept an affidavit attesting to under certain circumstances; increasing the
8 maximum amount of gross income of a charitable organization at which the
9 Secretary of State may require an audit or review of the charitable organization; and
10 generally relating to audit and review thresholds for charitable organizations.
11 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
12 Article – Business Regulation
13 Section 6–402(a)
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
17 Article – Business Regulation
18 Section 6–402(b)(7), (c)(1)(v), and (d)
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0483*

2 HOUSE BILL 483
1 Article – Business Regulation
2 6–402.
3 (a) A registration statement shall be on the form that the Secretary of State
4 provides.
5 (b) Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, the registration statement
6 shall contain or be accompanied by:
7 (7) (i) an audit by an independent certified public accountant if the
8 gross income from charitable contributions in the most recently completed fiscal year is at
9 least [$750,000] $1,000,000; or
10 (ii) a review by an independent certified public accountant if the
11 gross income from charitable contributions in the most recently completed fiscal year is at
12 least [$300,000] $500,000 $400,000 but less than [$750,000] $1,000,000;
13 (c) The Secretary of State may accept other documentation in place of any item
14 required under subsection (b) of this section, including, in place of the audit or review
15 required by subsection (b)(7) of this section, supporting documents indicating, and an
16 affidavit attesting, that:
17 (1) the charitable organization:
18 (v) has cash receipts from charitable contributions not exceeding
19 [$300,000] $500,000 $400,000 and amounting to 20% or less of the charitable
20 organization’s gross income during the immediately preceding fiscal year that are used for
21 program services or management and general expenses of the charitable organization, as
22 set forth under COMAR 01.02.04.04.A and C;
23 (d) The Secretary of State may require an audit or review if the amount of gross
24 income is less than [$750,000] $1,000,000.
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
26 1, 2026.

